## Executive Summary

The Republic of Korea is a growing humanitarian donor with an average
annual funding around \$7.5 million, demonstrating a clear upward trend
in geographic reach—supporting nearly 14 countries by 2025 compared to 8
in 2022. Its 2025 earmarked funding totals \$91.8 million, heavily
concentrated in East Asia, though with regional disparities. Compared to
peers, Korea provides a substantial volume of flexible funding, offering
versatility but less targeted earmarking. However, its funding frequency
and average transaction size are relatively low, indicating potential
volatility and limited reliability. Fundraisers should emphasize Korea’s
expanding engagement, advocate for increased and more consistent
contributions, and tailor proposals to leverage its flexible funding
pattern.

## Volatility

The visualization depicts funding transactions by the Republic of Korea
